---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const products = [
  {
    name: 'Boxing Gloves',
    why: `Your gloves protect your hands and your sparring partner's face. Both matter. The wrong gloves cause wrist injuries and joint pain that sideline beginners within weeks. Bag gloves and sparring gloves are different products; if you're only buying one pair, get a 12oz or 14oz all-purpose glove. Weight matters: heavier gloves (16oz) are required for most sparring scenarios.`,
    topPickReason: `The dual-closure wrist system provides real wrist support that beginners immediately notice, and the leather construction holds up to bag work far longer than entry-level synthetics.`,
    options: [
      { tier: 'Budget', name: 'Everlast Pro Style Training Gloves', price: '$30–40', bestFor: 'Reliable beginner glove, works for bag and pads', link: '#', retailer: "Buy at Dick's Sporting Goods →" },
      { tier: 'Mid-Range', name: 'Hayabusa T3 Boxing Gloves', price: '$100–120', bestFor: 'Excellent wrist support, durable leather, big step up', link: '#', retailer: 'Buy on Amazon →' },
      { tier: 'Premium', name: 'Cleto Reyes Hook and Loop Gloves', price: '$180–220', bestFor: 'Mexican-made leather, gym standard for serious training', link: '#', retailer: 'Buy at Title Boxing →' },
    ],
  },
  {
    name: 'Hand Wraps',
    why: `Gloves alone are not enough. Hand wraps stabilize your wrist, compress your knuckles, and protect your thumb joint. These are the parts of your hand that absorb impact before the glove padding does. Wear them every single session. 180" wraps are the right length for most adults; anything shorter leaves your wrist unsupported.`,
    topPickReason: `The 180-inch length gives full knuckle-to-wrist coverage that shorter wraps cannot match, and the stretch cotton conforms to your hand shape over time.`,
    options: [
      { tier: 'Budget', name: 'Everlast 120" Cotton Hand Wraps', price: '$8–12', bestFor: 'Gets the job done, machine washable, easy to find', link: '#', retailer: "Buy at Dick's Sporting Goods →" },
      { tier: 'Mid-Range', name: 'Title Boxing Mexican Style Hand Wraps', price: '$14–18', bestFor: '180" stretch cotton, superior compression and wrist coverage', link: '#', retailer: 'Buy at Title Boxing →' },
      { tier: 'Premium', name: 'Venum Kontact Gel Wraps', price: '$28–35', bestFor: 'Slip-on design with gel knuckle pad, fastest to put on before class', link: '#', retailer: 'Buy on Amazon →' },
    ],
  },
  {
    name: 'Mouthguard',
    why: `Non-negotiable for any sparring. It is a good idea even for bag work. You clench your jaw harder than you think on heavy shots, and a mouthguard prevents tooth grinding and jaw stress. Don't use the $5 boil-and-bite from a convenience store. Fit matters. A guard that fits poorly won't stay in and gives you false confidence.`,
    topPickReason: `Thin enough to breathe and talk through during sparring, which sounds minor until you're trying to receive instruction from a coach mid-round.`,
    options: [
      { tier: 'Budget', name: 'Shock Doctor Gel Max Mouthguard', price: '$18–25', bestFor: 'Best boil-and-bite on the market, tight custom fit', link: '#', retailer: "Buy at Dick's Sporting Goods →" },
      { tier: 'Mid-Range', name: 'SISU Aero 1.6mm Mouthguard', price: '$28–35', bestFor: 'Thin profile, can talk and drink with it in', link: '#', retailer: 'Buy on Amazon →' },
      { tier: 'Premium', name: 'SISU Max 2.4mm Mouthguard', price: '$35–45', bestFor: 'Maximum protection, same slim profile as Aero', link: '#', retailer: 'Buy at SISU →' },
    ],
  },
  {
    name: 'Jump Rope',
    why: `Jump rope is the standard boxing conditioning tool for a reason: it builds footwork, coordination, and cardiovascular endurance simultaneously. Ten minutes of jump rope is harder than it looks. Beginners should start with a basic speed rope. The weighted fitness jump ropes are a different training tool and not what boxing coaches use.`,
    topPickReason: `Ball-bearing handles and a fast wire cable let you build the rotational speed that boxing conditioning requires, at a price that makes sense before you fully commit to the sport.`,
    options: [
      { tier: 'Budget', name: 'XYLsports Jump Rope', price: '$8–12', bestFor: 'Lightweight speed rope, adjustable, fine to learn on', link: '#', retailer: 'Buy on Amazon →' },
      { tier: 'Mid-Range', name: 'Rx Smart Gear Jump Rope', price: '$35–50', bestFor: 'Bearing handles, fast wire cable, used by serious athletes', link: '#', retailer: 'Buy at Rx Smart Gear →' },
      { tier: 'Premium', name: 'Crossrope Get Lean Set', price: '$98–118', bestFor: 'Interchangeable weighted ropes, app workouts, best system', link: '#', retailer: 'Buy at Crossrope →' },
    ],
  },
  {
    name: 'Heavy Bag',
    why: `If you're training at home, a bag changes everything. Shadowboxing is useful but hitting something real teaches you about power transfer, distance, and proper form in a way nothing else does. A 70lb bag is right for most adults. It is heavy enough to not swing wildly on every punch and light enough to install without a structural engineer. Make sure your ceiling can handle the mount.`,
    topPickReason: `No ceiling mount required means you can set it up in any room without involving a structural engineer, and the weighted base provides real stability on any floor.`,
    options: [
      { tier: 'Budget', name: 'Everlast 70lb Heavy Bag Kit', price: '$80–110', bestFor: 'Includes gloves and wraps, good starter combo', link: '#', retailer: "Buy at Dick's Sporting Goods →" },
      { tier: 'Mid-Range', name: 'Century Wavemaster Freestanding Bag', price: '$180–220', bestFor: 'No ceiling mount needed, base fills with sand or water', link: '#', retailer: "Buy at Dick's Sporting Goods →" },
      { tier: 'Premium', name: 'Ringside 100lb Powerhide Heavy Bag', price: '$180–240', bestFor: 'Serious weight for serious training, durable leather cover', link: '#', retailer: 'Buy at Ringside →' },
    ],
  },
];

const tierColors: Record<string, string> = {
  Budget: 'bg-green-50 text-green-700',
  'Mid-Range': 'bg-blue-50 text-blue-700',
  Premium: 'bg-purple-50 text-purple-700',
};
---

<Layout
  title="Boxing Starter Kit | fitness-complete.com"
  description="Protect your hands first. Everything else is secondary. The exact gear a beginner boxer needs, researched from real fighters and real reviews."
>

  <!-- Nav -->
  <header class="border-b border-gray-100">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="/" class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900">fitness-complete</a>
      <nav class="hidden sm:flex gap-6 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <a href="/gym-starter-set" class="hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors">Gym</a>
        <a href="/pilates-starter-set" class="hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors">Pilates</a>
        <a href="/running-starter-set" class="hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors">Running</a>
        <a href="/home-gym-starter-set" class="hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors">Home Gym</a>
        <a href="/boxing-starter-set" class="text-gray-900 font-semibold transition-colors">Boxing</a>
        <a href="/gifts" class="hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors font-medium text-gray-700">🎁 Gifts</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pt-16 pb-12">
      <a href="/" class="inline-block text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-600 transition-colors mb-6">← All starter kits</a>
      <figure class="mb-8">
        <img
          src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1549719386-74dfcbf7dbed?w=800"
          alt="Boxer training with gloves and heavy bag"
          class="w-full rounded-2xl object-cover max-h-[400px]"
        />
        <figcaption class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-2">Photo: Unsplash</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 mb-3">Boxing</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900 leading-tight mb-5">
        Boxing Starter Kit
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-500 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        Protect your hands first. Everything else is secondary.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Methodology intro -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pb-12">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-100">
        <h2 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">How these picks were made</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
          These picks were researched across four sources: Reddit community discussions, independent test sites (Garage Gym Reviews, CNN Underscored, Wirecutter), Amazon verified purchase reviews filtered for 3-star honesty and long-term durability, and YouTube reviews from channels without sponsorship conflicts. Commission rate played no role.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Product sections -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pb-16 space-y-16">

      {products.map((product, i) => (
        <div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="bg-gray-900 text-white text-xs font-bold w-6 h-6 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
              {i + 1}
            </span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">{product.name}</h2>
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-5 max-w-3xl">{product.why}</p>

          <!-- Top pick callout -->
          <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-100 rounded-xl p-4 mb-6">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-blue-600 mb-1">Our top pick</p>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-sm">{product.options[1].name}</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">{product.topPickReason}</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Comparison table — desktop -->
          <div class="hidden sm:block overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-gray-100">
            <table class="w-full text-sm">
              <thead>
                <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-100">
                  <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 font-semibold text-gray-500 w-24">Tier</th>
                  <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 font-semibold text-gray-500">Product</th>
                  <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 font-semibold text-gray-500 w-32">Price</th>
                  <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 font-semibold text-gray-500">Best For</th>
                  <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 font-semibold text-gray-500 w-24">Link</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                {product.options.map((opt, j) => (
                  <tr class={j < product.options.length - 1 ? 'border-b border-gray-100' : ''}>
                    <td class="px-5 py-4">
                      <span class={`inline-block text-xs font-semibold px-2 py-1 rounded-full ${tierColors[opt.tier]}`}>
                        {opt.tier}
                      </span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="px-5 py-4 font-medium text-gray-900">{opt.name}</td>
                    <td class="px-5 py-4 text-gray-500">{opt.price}</td>
                    <td class="px-5 py-4 text-gray-500">{opt.bestFor}</td>
                    <td class="px-5 py-4">
                      <a href={opt.link} class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 font-semibold transition-colors">
                        {opt.retailer}
                      </a>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                ))}
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <!-- Comparison cards — mobile -->
          <div class="sm:hidden space-y-3">
            {product.options.map((opt) => (
              <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-100 p-4">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
                  <span class={`inline-block text-xs font-semibold px-2 py-1 rounded-full ${tierColors[opt.tier]}`}>
                    {opt.tier}
                  </span>
                  <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 font-medium">{opt.price}</span>
                </div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-sm mb-1">{opt.name}</p>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-3">{opt.bestFor}</p>
                <a href={opt.link} class="inline-block text-sm font-semibold text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 transition-colors">
                  {opt.retailer}
                </a>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}

    </section>

    <!-- Gift callout -->
    <section class="bg-amber-50 border-t border-amber-100">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-6">
        <div class="w-1 self-stretch bg-amber-300 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 hidden sm:block"></div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Gift this kit</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base max-w-2xl">
            Know someone who just joined a boxing gym or wants to start training at home? A pair of Everlast gloves and hand wraps is a complete, under-$50 gift that shows you thought about what they actually need. Add a jump rope and you've covered their first month of conditioning.
          </p>
          <a href="/gifts" class="inline-block mt-3 text-sm font-semibold text-amber-700 hover:text-amber-900 transition-colors">
            See the full gift guide →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="border-t border-gray-100">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-8 space-y-4">
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center justify-between gap-4">
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-900">fitness-complete.com</p>
        <div class="flex gap-5 text-xs">
          <a href="/about" class="text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-600 transition-colors">About</a>
          <a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-600 transition-colors">Privacy Policy</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center justify-between gap-2">
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">This site contains affiliate links. We may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Last updated: March 2026</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

</Layout>
